OL,3,CPokemon cards: The growing popularity
OL,4,Cof a children's toy said to outpace
OL,5,Cgold
OL,7,FOne collector, known online as the
OL,8,FKabuto King, recently set himself the
OL,9,Fmission of collecting every first
OL,10,Fedition copy of an otherwise fairly
OL,11,Fcommon and cheap-to-purchase card.
OL,13,FKabuto King began collecting cards of
OL,14,Fthe Pokemon called Kabuto in early
OL,15,FAugust, 2025. By the end of the month,
OL,16,Fhis collection stood at 737 cards. But
OL,17,Fat the time, he claimed it was getting
OL,18,Fharder to find them to buy.
OL,26,@kD@DrrvD@Hrr
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G28/37
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31729
SC,0029
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1772220031
OL,3,CPokemon cards: The growing popularity
OL,4,Cof a children's toy said to outpace
OL,5,Cgold
OL,7,FOn February 17, his collection was
OL,8,F3,543 strong, with the average price
OL,9,Fof the card shooting up to $18.12
OL,10,F(#13.47) from $2.96 (#2.15) for an
OL,11,Fungraded copy and $854.65 (#635.10)
OL,12,Ffrom $80.50 (#58.45) for mint
OL,13,Fcondition, respectively.
OL,15,FKabuto King has previously signalled
OL,16,Fhe has no plans to sell his
OL,17,Fcollection, despite the increased
OL,18,Fprice of his cards.
OL,26,@kD@Drr
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G29/37
